message: Focus on combining items with similar features (e.g., natural with natural, artificial with artificial) first. Avoid combining items with mixed natural/artificial features directly, as this often results in very low values. The 'frame' tool is very powerful; use it on combined items (especially those with 0 value) to significantly increase their value. 'Scissors' can make values negative but sometimes sets them up for 'frame' to improve them. Often, the best strategy is to create two distinct combined items (one natural, one artificial), frame both, and then submit, rather than combining the framed items.
